sections.text: Terms, defined.As used in the Missing Children Identification Act, unless the context otherwise requires:(1) County agency means any agency in a county that records and maintains birth certificates;(2) Department means the Department of Health and Human Services;(3) Missing person means a person sixteen years of age or younger reported to any law enforcement agency as abducted or lost; and(4) Patrol means the Nebraska State Patrol.SourceLaws 1987, LB 599, ยง 3;Laws 1996, LB 1044, ยง 208;Laws 1997, LB 307, ยง 83;Laws 2007, LB296, ยง 137.
